title: Warmer than normal Saturday in store for Winnipeg -
text:
It may be a cool start to the day, but just give it time because you will be raking leaves in temperatures warmer than usual.
Environment Canada is predicting a high of 17 C under sunny skies today, a full three degrees higher than the normal average high of 14 C. At 9 a.m. the mercury was siting at just under 7 C.
Tonight the temperature will bottom out at 6 C, then rebound during Sunday to 14 C. Sunday night is expected to drop to 9 C with a 40 per cent chance of showers.
The week ahead will see temperatures around the mid-teens with highs of 15 C on Monday, 13 C on Tuesday, 15 C on Wednesday, 16 C on Thursday and 17 C on Friday.
The mercury reached 17.7 C in Winnipeg on Friday.
While the temperature will be warmer than normal today, it will come nowhere near the record setting temperature of 28.3 C in 1976.
Mind you, thatâ€™s better than hitting the record cold temperature of -6.9 C in 1999.
